<TITLE> Kushtia 'extremist' killed in shootout </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, Aug 25 (bdnews24.com)  An extremist of the outlawed Gano Bahini (Lal) party was killed in a shoot out with police in Kushtia early Tuesday. Kushtia police super Shahabuddin Khan said the deceased, 35-year old Shahinur Rahman Dablu, was shot near Milpara crematorium. Police were tipped off that a group of armed militants were entering the town from Haripur village, Khan said. Kushtia Sadar police intercepted the gang near the crematorium at around 4am. "The gang opened fire at police and the police fired back." "At one point Shahin was shot and died on the spot. Others fled the scene," said Khan. Police recovered one a firearm and 10 rounds of ammunition from the spot, he said. Sadar police said there were a number of cases against Shahin on charges of extortion, mugging and robbing. Police sent Shahin's body to Kushtia General Hospital morgue. Another extremist was killed in a gunfight with police Friday night at Doulatpur Upazila in Kushtia. bdn
